==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rock shaft
<hw>Rock" shaft`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Cf. <er>Rock</er>, <ets>v.
i.</ets>]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A shaft that oscillates on its
journals, instead of revolving, -- usually carrying levers by means of
which it receives and communicates reciprocating motion, as in the valve
gear of some steam engines; -- called also <altname>rocker</altname>,
<altname>rocking shaft</altname>, and <altname>way
shaft</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rock staff</ent>⟦br⟧
